{"parse":{"title":"Elitzur's theorem","pageid":31583410,"revid":781610146,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Orphan\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"display: none\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Orphan\" title=\"Wikipedia:Orphan\">orphan</a>, as no other articles <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere&amp;target=Elitzur%27s_theorem&amp;namespace=0\">link to it</a></b>. Please <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Link\" title=\"Help:Link\">introduce links</a> to this page from <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&amp;redirs=1&amp;search=Elitzur%26%2339%3Bs+theorem&amp;fulltext=Search&amp;ns0=1&amp;title=Special%3ASearch&amp;advanced=1&amp;fulltext=Elitzur%26%2339%3Bs+theorem\">related articles</a></span>; try the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//edwardbetts.com/find_link?q=Elitzur%27s_theorem\">Find link tool</a> for suggestions.  <small><i>(April 2011)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Elitzur's theorem</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Theorem\" title=\"Theorem\">theorem</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Quantum_field_theory\" title=\"Quantum field theory\">quantum</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Statistical_field_theory\" title=\"Statistical field theory\">statistical field theory</a> stating that local <a href=\"/wiki/Gauge_theory\" title=\"Gauge theory\">gauge symmetries</a> cannot be <a href=\"/wiki/Spontaneous_symmetry_breaking\" title=\"Spontaneous symmetry breaking\">spontaneously broken</a>. The theorem was proposed in 1975 by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shmuel_Elitzur&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Shmuel Elitzur (page does not exist)\">Shmuel Elitzur</a>, who proved it for <a href=\"/wiki/Abelian_group\" title=\"Abelian group\">Abelian</a> gauge fields on a <a href=\"/wiki/Lattice_gauge_theory\" title=\"Lattice gauge theory\">lattice</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is nonetheless possible to spontaneously break a global symmetry within a theory that has a local gauge symmetry, as in the <a href=\"/wiki/Higgs_mechanism\" title=\"Higgs mechanism\">Higgs mechanism</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2015)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elitzur%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Mermin%E2%80%93Wagner_theorem\" title=\"Mermin\u2013Wagner theorem\">Mermin\u2013Wagner theorem</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elitzur%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Elitzur S (1975). \"Impossibility of spontaneously breaking local symmetries\". <i>Phys. Rev. D</i>. <b>12</b>: 3978\u20133982. <a href=\"/wiki/Bibcode\" title=\"Bibcode\">Bibcode</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1975PhRvD..12.3978E\">1975PhRvD..12.3978E</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevD.12.3978\">10.1103/PhysRevD.12.3978</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Phys.+Rev.+D&amp;rft.atitle=Impossibility+of+spontaneously+breaking+local+symmetries&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.pages=3978-3982&amp;rft.date=1975&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1103%2FPhysRevD.12.3978&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F1975PhRvD..12.3978E&amp;rft.au=Elitzur+S&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AElitzur%27s+theorem\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Elitzur%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite id=\"CITEREFItzyksonDrouffe1989\" class=\"citation\">Itzykson, Claude; Drouffe, Jean-Michel (1989), <i>Statistical field theory. Vol. 1</i>, Cambridge Monographs on Mathematical Physics, <a href=\"/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press\" title=\"Cambridge University Press\">Cambridge University Press</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-521-34058-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-521-34058-8\">978-0-521-34058-8</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews\" title=\"Mathematical Reviews\">MR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1175176\">1175176</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Statistical+field+theory.+Vol.+1&amp;rft.series=Cambridge+Monographs+on+Mathematical+Physics&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-521-34058-8&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fmathscinet-getitem%3Fmr%3D1175176&amp;rft.aulast=Itzykson&amp;rft.aufirst=Claude&amp;rft.au=Drouffe%2C+Jean-Michel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AElitzur%27s+theorem\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"E